# Motion Footer

Cinematic sticky reveal footer that appears underneath the main content via clip-path. Features a GSAP ScrollTrigger parallax on giant background text, staggered content reveal, diagonal marquee ticker, magnetic glass-pill CTA buttons (GSAP spring hover), aurora glow, grid background, and a heartbeat heart animation. Theme-adaptive using CSS custom properties.

## Use when
- Adding a visually striking footer to a dark SaaS or product landing page.
- Creating a scroll-revealed footer that emerges as users finish the page.
- Showcasing download CTAs with magnetic hover interactions.

## Stack
- Framework: react
- Libraries: gsap
- Requires: tailwind

## Install
```bash
gsap
```

## Component — motion-footer.tsx
```tsx
"use client";

import * as React from "react";
import { useEffect, useRef } from "react";
import { gsap } from "gsap";
import { ScrollTrigger } from "gsap/ScrollTrigger";
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

if (typeof window !== "undefined") {
  gsap.registerPlugin(ScrollTrigger);
}

// STYLES constant contains: .cinematic-footer-wrapper, .footer-bg-grid,
// .footer-aurora, .footer-glass-pill, .footer-giant-bg-text, .footer-text-glow,
// @keyframes footer-breathe, footer-scroll-marquee, footer-heartbeat

export type MagneticButtonProps = React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement> & 
  React.AnchorHTMLAttributes<HTMLAnchorElement> & {
    as?: React.ElementType;
  };

const MagneticButton = React.forwardRef<HTMLElement, MagneticButtonProps>(
  ({ className, children, as: Component = "button", ...props }, forwardedRef) => {
    const localRef = useRef<HTMLElement>(null);
    useEffect(() => {
      // GSAP magnetic hover: mousemove -> translateX/Y + rotationX/Y, mouseleave -> elastic reset
    }, []);
    return <Component ref={/* merged ref */} className={cn("cursor-pointer", className)} {...props}>{children}</Component>;
  }
);
MagneticButton.displayName = "MagneticButton";

export function CinematicFooter() {
  const wrapperRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    // GSAP ScrollTrigger: giant text parallax + staggered content reveal
  }, []);

  return (
    <>
      <style dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: STYLES }} />
      <div ref={wrapperRef} className="relative h-screen w-full" style={{ clipPath: "polygon(0% 0, 100% 0%, 100% 100%, 0 100%)" }}>
        <footer className="fixed bottom-0 left-0 flex h-screen w-full flex-col justify-between overflow-hidden bg-background text-foreground cinematic-footer-wrapper">
          {/* aurora, grid, giant bg text, marquee, CTAs, bottom bar */}
        </footer>
      </div>
    </>
  );
}
```

## Demo
```tsx
"use client";

import { CinematicFooter } from "@/components/ui/motion-footer";

export default function Demo() {
  return (
    <div className="relative w-full bg-background min-h-screen overflow-x-hidden">
      <main className="relative z-10 w-full min-h-[120vh] bg-background flex flex-col items-center justify-center border-b border-white/10 rounded-b-3xl">
        <h1 className="text-4xl font-light tracking-[0.2em] text-neutral-400 mb-8 uppercase text-center px-4">
          Scroll down to reveal
        </h1>
        <div className="w-[1px] h-32 bg-gradient-to-b from-neutral-400 to-transparent" />
      </main>
      <CinematicFooter />
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Notes
- The sticky footer uses `position: fixed` with a `clip-path` wrapper to create the curtain-reveal effect. The footer is always positioned at the bottom of the viewport, revealed as the user scrolls past the main content.
- All CSS is injected via `<style dangerouslySetInnerHTML>` including custom `@keyframes` and CSS custom property variables for theming.
- Uses `color-mix(in oklch, ...)` for theme-adaptive colors — requires a browser supporting CSS color-mix (Chrome 111+, Firefox 113+, Safari 16.2+).
- `footer` is a new placement value not in the PROTOCOL.md seed list.
